thread.title: Prep Softball: St. Elizabeth advances to district title game

author: News Tribune
title: Prep Softball: St. Elizabeth advances to district title game
text:
Share 
ST. ELIZABETH, Mo. — The St. Elizabeth Lady Hornets downed Newburg 11-1 in five innings Thursday in the semifinals of the Class 1 District 3 Tournament. 
With the win, St. Elizabeth (7-14) advances to tonight’s title game against Crocker. Game time is 6 p.m. 
Regan Wilde was the winning pitcher, striking out eight. Wilde also had two hits and three RBI. Courtney Scheulen had three hits and two RBI in the win. Amber Struemph and Kaylee Chitman also had two hits and three RBI. ﻿
